{
  "text": "where Pcarb is the potential carbon production and RUEs is crop-specific radiation use efficiency (given in Table 2 ). In the equations above, RUEs is modified according to various DF-to-\u2206RUE relationships. We calculate the net effect of PM on crop production across three levels of impact: max \u2206RUE = 0 % (changes in SW only, the direct effect (always negative)), max \u2206RUE = 50 % (maximum 1.5 \u00d7 RUE enhancement at DF = 0.8), and max \u2206RUE = 100 % (maximum 2 \u00d7 RUE enhancement 25 at DF = 0.8) based on literature values [CITATION_1] . Finally, we calculate the RY due to PM as the relative total Pcarb with PM compared to without PM for each crop under each relationship (Eq. 6).",
